-- HSBC Names Vrettou for Greece as Politis Joins Credit Suisse
-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 2012-05-22T11:53:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/hsbc-names-vrettou-for-greece-as-politis-joins-credit-suisse.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Europe’s largest
bank, named Eleni Vrettou as head of global banking for Greece
after Dimitris Politis left to join  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) ’s
private bank.  Vrettou will assume the position in June, an HSBC spokesman
in London said. At Credit Suisse, Politis is covering Greek
clients, offering dealmaking advice to complement the bank’s
asset-management services, a spokesman for the Zurich-based
company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi in Milan at 
